Meet Joanna.

Joanna has been a tattoo artist for 6 years, specializing in fine line tattoos. Recently, she was diagnosed with  Crohn’s disease, which affected every aspect of her life. She was unable to tattoo and living day to day. 

Chronic House grew out of the idea of being reborn — the opportunity to extend the talent of our artists at Chronic Ink and give them a new life.

“This is where I say fuck you to crohns. I want to feel like myself again. I want to feel alive. I don’t want to feel caged to my bed and watch life pass me by. I just want to design things and spread my art all over the world.

I hope you like these pieces because for me they are more than just jewelry. Butterflies are my most requested designs and I want these butterflies to make people feel alive.” — Jojo

🦋CHRONIC HOUSE🦋 

#jojotattoo #tattoojewellery

A powerful beacon of strength and hopefulness in new beginnings, the butterfly symbolizes our rebirth.

When @joannamroman got diagnosed with Crohn’s disease, it affected every aspect of her life. It got to the point where she was living day to day and didn’t know if she could tattoo until she woke up. 

“Anyone who’s dealt with a chronic illness will understand the toll it takes on you. But thanks to my family, friends, and clients. They have given me the strength to fight back.” - Joanna

And now we are also doing our part in the fight against Crohn’s disease. With every purchase of the Harry ring, we will donate a portion of the sales to Crohn’s and Colitis Canada

The only national, volunteer-based charity focused on finding the cures for Crohn’s disease and ulcerative colitis and improving the lives of children and adults affected by these diseases.🦋
